items.checkin_comment: Can never go wrong with peacharine hops. Quite dry, very easy drinking as it should be and a big peach hit as expected also. It’s the equivalent of the Test Prints little brother

user.bio: Sipping my way through this large world of craft beer, minus the hipster pretense
Love trying all the different beers, and dont mind a good scotch. Ratings are mine on style and taste for that style.

items.checkin_comment: Pours a fairly thick haze with a fragile head. Flavours are pretty good for the ABV, featuring stonefruit, citrus, grape, berry. Slightly dry, very smashable as a balcony beer should be!
Tasty 5% hazy, plenty of flavour for the ABV.
